</h2>
<h3>
    <strong>Seasonal Patterns in the Pacific Northwest</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    Largemouth bass exhibit different behaviors depending on the season. Spring marks the spawn, when bass move to shallower areas to nest. Summer brings aggressive feeding behavior, while fall sees bass transitioning deeper before winter.
</p>
<h3>
    <strong>Feeding Habits and Preferred Habitat</strong>
</h3>
<p>
    These opportunistic feeders prefer slow-moving or still waters with plenty of cover—think submerged logs, weed beds, and lily pads. Early morning and late evening are prime times for feeding, especially in warmer months.
</p>
